filter_genotypes_and_variants_wecare_only

started: Alexey Larionov, 01Mar2016
last updated: Alexey Larionov, 10Apr2017

Summary

The filters are applied in the following order:
1) gq > 20
2) dp < 500
3) call_rate > 0.8
4) remove variants with uniform genotypes accross all samples:
- most of those were in NFE only
- some might be created by the above filtering steps

gq 20 filter is set arbitrary; however, it is consistent with what some othersis do
(e.g.see Carson BMC Bioinformatics. 2014 15:125).

A small number of genotypes (<<1%) was covered too high to be true (up to 1-2k coverage). These are obvious mistakes, and they have been removed too. Arbitrarily the threshold for max DP was set to 500 (appr. 10 fold of average coverage).

It was discussed with DC whether to filter cases by call rate per case. There was ~3 cases with low coverage (<20) and low call rates (<50%). We desided to keep such cases because their retained genotypes still passed all filters.

Input data: 343,824 vars x 512 cases
Output data: 255,043 vars x 512 cases
